Title : Giovanni Domenico Ferracuti
Text : '''Giovanni Domenico Ferracuti''' (mid to late17th century)  was an [[Italy|Italian]] painter, active in [[Macerata]] concentrating on landscapes, especially on wintry landscapes.

He was a follower of [[Gaspard Dughet]] and collaborated with figure painter [[Pier Simone Fanelli]] in painting for San Giorgio in Macerata.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=boNAAAAAYAAJ Memorie storiche delle arti e degli artisti della Marca di Ancona]. by Amico Ricci page 296.</ref>

